---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '@/components/Hero.astro';
import CTABlock from '@/components/CTABlock.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="My Lush Story"
  description="How a trip to Creative Showcase in 2016 turned into a full-blown Lush obsession, a Kitchen subscription, and a TikTok."
>
  <Hero
    title="My Lush Story"
    tag="The origin story"
    minimal
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <div class="page-content">
        <p>
          I wasn't always this deep into Lush. Like most people in the UK, I knew the shops. You
          walk past and the smell hits you from three doors down. I'd bought the odd bath bomb
          as a gift, maybe grabbed a soap here and there. But I wasn't properly into it.
        </p>

        <h3>Creative Showcase, 2016</h3>
        <p>
          Everything changed when I went to Lush Creative Showcase in 2016. If you haven't heard
          of it, it was basically this massive event where Lush showed off new products, let you
          meet the people who actually make everything, and generally went all-in on the creative
          side of the brand.
        </p>
        <p>
          I went not really knowing what to expect and came back genuinely buzzing. Seeing how
          products are developed, watching people hand-make bath bombs, understanding the
          whole ethos behind it, and it properly clicked. I went from "Lush is that shop that
          smells nice" to actually caring about the products and the stories behind them.
        </p>

        <h3>Lush Showcase, 2018</h3>
        <p>
          Two years later I went to Lush Showcase 2018 and that sealed it. By this point I was
          properly invested. I knew product names, scent families, what was discontinued when. The
          2018 event was incredible. Meeting other fans who were equally obsessed, discovering products
          I'd never even heard of, getting hands-on with everything.
        </p>
        <p>
          That event took me from "interested fan" to "yeah this is a proper hobby now." No regrets.
        </p>

        <h3>The gap years</h3>
        <p>
          I'll be honest, between 2018 and 2022 I was still buying Lush but I wasn't as tuned in.
          Life happens, you drift a bit. I'd still pick up favourites when I was in a shop, still
          had opinions about seasonal ranges, but I wasn't keeping up with every launch.
        </p>

        <h3>February 2022: Kitchen arrives</h3>
        <p>
          When the Kitchen subscription launched, something switched back on. The idea of a monthly
          box of exclusive and returning products was basically designed for people like me. I
          subscribed in February 2022 and haven't missed a month since.
        </p>
        <p>
          The first few boxes reminded me why I fell for this stuff in the first place. Products I'd
          never tried, scents that took me back to Showcase, things I didn't even know I wanted. It
          reignited the whole thing.
        </p>

        <h3>Starting TikTok</h3>
        <p>
          I started filming unboxings on TikTok because honestly, I was already doing it in my head
          anyway. Every month the box would arrive and I'd have this whole internal monologue:
          first impressions, scent notes, what it reminds me of, whether the community would rate it.
          Figured I might as well film it.
        </p>
        <p>
          The TikTok isn't polished and it's not trying to be. It's just me opening a box and giving
          honest reactions. Sometimes I'm buzzing about a product, sometimes I'm a bit "hmm okay,"
          and both of those are fine. I'd rather be genuine than performative.
        </p>

        <h3>What Lush means to me</h3>
        <p>
          I'm not going to be cheesy about it, but Lush is genuinely one of those things that just
          makes life a bit better. A good bath bomb at the end of a long day, a soap that smells
          incredible, a product that takes you back to a specific memory. That stuff matters more
          than people give it credit for.
        </p>
        <p>
          This site exists because those moments deserve to be documented somewhere. Not as reviews,
          not as content, just as a record of a thing I properly love.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABlock
    title="Browse the archive"
    description="Every Kitchen box since February 2022. Products, scent notes, nostalgia, the lot."
    primaryLink="/kitchen-boxes/"
    primaryLabel="Kitchen Boxes"
    secondaryLink="/what-is-kitchen/"
    secondaryLabel="What is Kitchen?"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-content h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .page-content p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    max-width: none;
  }
</style>
